        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         "There was no nerf on dire charm."</P><P>Actually, no.  Dire charmed pets as it previously was would take 50% of the exp, maximum, if no player did any damage.  Now, if no player does any damage, dire charmed pets, like normal pets, take 75% of the exp, maximum.  As Rich said, dire charmed pets *also* take exp proportional to the amount of damage dealt.  Therefore, if dire charmed pets do the majority of damage (e.g. in the case of enchanters most likely), it could very well take more than 50% of the exp.</P><P>Overall, very nice fundamental changes, though I think it is possible that some might be pissed that they can no longer solo efficiently with dire charmed pets (though really, they never were able to).  An important question here is, as mentioned above, whether this applies to normal charmed pets as well, which would suck because then charm soloing would no longer really be viable.(since charm soloing depends on conserving mana through letting the charmed pet do most of the damage)</P><P>The only thing left to fix for pets is their resistances and hps, though I really would appreciate it if pets pre-EoT would receive the same boosts the EoT received.  Mages had a complete revamp of ALL their post-50 pets, I think necromancers should too.</P><P>This has been a huge step forward in the way of balancing pet classes on part of Verant, and I thank you, Rich/Jahaar, for telling us about it.</P><P><BR>Etadanik the Redeemed</P><P>Edited by - Etadanik Mistmorgue on 06/03/2002  08:25:53<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
